cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new approach to contrastive learning, which is a widely used strategy in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks. The paper specifically mentions examples of NLP tasks such as word embeddings and knowledge graph embeddings, which suggests that cs.CL and cs.AI are likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions order embeddings, which are used in recommendation systems, and this could fall under cs.LG or cs.CV. Finally, the paper introduces an adversarial component to the negative sampler, which is a technique commonly used in generative models and could suggest cs.NE as a possible sub-category.
